A4.text: The Battle of Agincourt ( AJ-in-kor(t); French: Azincourt [azɛ̃kuʁ]) was an English victory in the Hundred Years' War.

A5.text: It took place on 25 October 1415 (Saint Crispin's Day) near Azincourt, in northern France.
